				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ E_{{\text{m}}} (i) = [(E + \varepsilon_{e} ) \times i] \times [(T + \varepsilon_{t} ) \times i] $$\end{document}where Em shows emergy value; E displays energy (J), mess (kg), and economical ($), respectively; T is emergy conversion rate, εe\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
